### General Info
***

Backend for frontend. It has been developed to give access to suscripcionAdidas Microservice methods. 

There are 4 different methods, running on port 8080:
* "/adidas/createSubscription" (Post) --> Create a new subscription. Json required:
	{
	"email":"",
	"first_name":"",
	"gender":"",
	"date_of_birth":"dd/MM/yyyy",
	"consent_flag":"",
	"newsletter_id":""
	}
* "/adidas/deleteSubscription/{id}" (Delete) --> Delete the given subscription
* "/adidas/subscriptions/{id}" (Get) --> List the given subscription
* "/adidas/subscriptions" (Get) --> List all the subscriptions

## Technologies
***
A list of libraries used within the project:
* [spring-boot-starter-web]: Used for restfull webservices with spring and a tomcat included
* [spring-boot-devtools]: Used for development. It allows you to run easily the application in the embedded tomcat.

## Installation
***
Running using docker.
Docker is an open platform for building, shipping and running distributed applications. Follow steps on the site to install docker based on your operating system.
The bffAdidas image depends on several images. Run also suscripcionAdidas image, mailAdidas and mysql image with the following scirpt:

version: "3"

services:
  mail-container:
    image: mailadidas
    ports:
      - 8082:8082
  mysql-standalone:
      image: mysql
      environment:
        - MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=rootpwd
        - MYSQL_USER= adidasusr
        - MYSQL_PASSWORD=adidaspwd
        - MYSQL_DATABASE=adidasdb
      ports:
        - 3306:3306
  suscripcion-container:
    image: suscripcionadidas
    restart: on-failure
    ports:
      - 8081:8081
    depends_on:
      - mysql-standalone
      - mail-container
  bff-container:
    image: bffadidas
    restart: on-failure
    ports:
      - 8080:8080
    depends_on:
      - suscripcion-container
